definitions.definition: A set amount of travelling, seen as a single unit; a discrete trip , a voyage .
examples: The journey to London takes two hours by train.

definitions.definition: ( figurative ) Any process or progression likened to a journey, especially one that involves difficulties or personal development .
examples: my journey of dealing with grief

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) A day's travelling; the distance travelled in a day.
The weight of finished coins delivered at one time to the Master of the Mint .
( collective , colloquial ) A group of giraffes .
